                    <span>I don't see why anyone should settle for second best.  I read anything and everything on how to be my best and bring out the best in others.  I really like the author's perspective of confronting  habits.  So much of our activity is automatic, based on old coping mechanisms. <p>This author recognizes that we do have the power to help others be their best and that self-limiting habits need to be conquered.  The reader is given a series of steps to take to overcome these habits.  Try them!</span>
                  
